body:
@gwenshap Updated to use the new approach to offsets we discussed. Also updated system test to be parameterized and test JSON and String serializers, including JSON with schemas and without schemas. Hopefully this covers enough bases that it's fairly good confirmation that we can make this work.

I'm honestly not enthusiastic about how the code for reading offsets looks since it's a bunch of checking for nulls and validating specific types, but maybe this is the best solution when we have to balance data with good schemas vs schemaless data.

I'm thinking maybe we can provide some utilities for converting maps with string fields to structs with some basic checks in place so it'll make connector implementors jobs' easier. What do you think about that?

@junrao, pushed two additional commits to address the two outstanding issues. I implemented things in a slightly different way than what was discussed. I added some comments to the PR explaining. Let me know what you think.

`gradlew test` passed locally and system tests passed too:

http://jenkins.confluent.io/job/kafka_system_tests_branch_builder/63/console
